This paper is about off-policy evaluation in reinforcement learning, which is a problem that falls under the umbrella of machine learning. The paper introduces a novel estimator based on statistical causal inference principles, which suggests that it may belong to the cs.LG (Machine Learning) sub-category. Additionally, the paper discusses variance reduction techniques, which could also place it in the cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) sub-category. The paper also mentions asymptotic distribution and rate of convergence, which are topics that fall under the cs.ST (Statistics) sub-category. Finally, the paper discusses empirical results across multiple environments, which could place it in the cs.CE (Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science) sub-category, and the paper's focus on reinforcement learning could also place it in the cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) sub-category.
